tion Act Amendments of 2017’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id62bc5d2f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Consultation With Indian Tribes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/58/tV/s504"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–58, title V, § 504","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/778"},"text":"119 Stat. 778","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/109/58/tV/s504"},"text":"“In carrying out this title [enacting this chapter, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s7144e"},"text":"section 7144e of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, and subchapter V (§ 16001) of chapter 149 of Title 42, amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s4132"},"text":"section 4132 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5315"},"text":"section 5315 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees, and enacting provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s15801"},"text":"section 15801 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":"] and the amendments made by this title, the Secretary [of Energy] and the Secretary of the Interior shall, as appropriate and to the maximum extent practicable, involve and consult with Indian tribes.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
